{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772071151,"nonce":"hxZklw7t6ocGdiBIzPHs+/ROMCY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87t_Wgf","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/265","origin":"github"},"title":"Add CI enforcement checks for workspace rules","message":"## Problem\n\nDesign decisions and workspace rules are documented but not mechanically enforced beyond branch protection and pre-commit hooks. The research identified several low-effort, high-value CI checks that would catch issues agents and humans currently miss.\n\n## Prior work\n\n- [ADR-0004](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/blob/feature/issue-249/docs/decisions/0004-enforcement-hierarchy-for-agent-compliance.md): Enforcement hierarchy — instructions → hooks → CI → containers\n- [ADR-0005](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/blob/feature/issue-249/docs/decisions/0005-layered-enforcement-strategy.md): Layered enforcement strategy\n- [Issue #249 research](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/249), §10 Phase 5: Prioritized list of CI checks\n\n## Scope (ordered by impact-to-effort)\n\n1. **File-change correlation CI check** — when certain files change together (e.g., \\`package.xml\\` + \\`CMakeLists.txt\\`), validate consistency\n2. **Structural validation** — referenced paths in docs actually exist\n3. **Layer dependency boundary check** — no upward dependencies in \\`package.xml\\`\n4. **Agent-teachable error messages** — all custom lint/CI failures include remediation instructions targeted at agent consumption\n\nEach of these can be a separate PR. The key insight from the research: items 1–4 are all deterministic traditional CI — AI-powered semantic review should wait until these structural checks are in place.\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Guided by [Principle #4: Enforcement over documentation](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/blob/feature/issue-249/docs/PRINCIPLES.md)\n- Guided by [Principle #5: Radical simplicity](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/blob/feature/issue-249/docs/PRINCIPLES.md) — don't over-engineer; start with the simplest useful check\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: \\`Claude Code Agent\\`\n**Model**: \\`Claude Opus 4.6\\`","files":null}]}